  "text": "Previous in vivo analysis of negative selection by peptide injection has been hampered by cytokine-and glucocorticoidmediated thymocyte apoptosis resulting from more protracted and repetitive activation of peripheral T cells [CITATION_1] . While we cannot completely rule out effects of peripheral T cells in our in vivo model, we believe that these are negligible for the following reasons. (i) Cytokine-and glucocorticoid-mediated thymocyte apoptosis by peripheral T cells has been described upon repetitive activation, i.e. three consecutive injections of peptide [CITATION_2] ; in contrast, we induce negative selection by a single injection of VSV8. (ii) We use a 4 times lower concentration of peptide than Martin and Bevan. (iii) Cytokine-and glucocorticoid-mediated thymocyte apoptosis by peripheral T cells occurs within days (55); we analyzed gene induction in a time frame of a few hours. (iv) We observe deletion of DP thymocytes in N15 H-2 b mice in FTOC, i.e. in the absence of peripheral T cells.",
